## Current story

**ID:** STORY-001
**Title:** Fix glassmorphic transparency and visual foundation
**Description:** The current UI is opaque and does not use proper macOS vibrancy. Fix NSVisualEffectView configuration, set window background to clear, ensure all panels use `.hudWindow` or `.sidebar` material, and remove all hardcoded gray backgrounds that kill the glass effect.

**Acceptance criteria:**
- Main window background is transparent/vibrancy-backed — no solid gray or black fill visible behind panels
- All three columns use NSVisualEffectView with appropriate material (sidebar left, fullScreenUI center, hudWindow right)
- Window title bar is hidden or uses unified style — clean macOS 15 look
- TimedCard uses translucent fill (Color(.windowBackgroundColor).opacity(0.45)) not a solid Color(.controlBackgroundColor)
- App builds and launches without visual regressions

**Implementation notes:**
The key fix is in VisualEffectView.swift and ContentView.swift. The window must be set to .titled | .fullSizeContentView and backgroundColor = .clear. NSHostingView background should also be cleared. In ContentView, replace any Color(.controlBackground) fills with Color.clear or a very low-opacity white. The TimedCard component in TimedCard.swift should use `.ultraThinMaterial` background. Check that all ZStack/VStack backgrounds are not accidentally opaque. In TimeManagerDesktopApp.swift, configure the WindowGroup with .windowStyle(.hiddenTitleBar) or equivalent.

