**ID:** STORY-002
**Title:** Redesign 3-pane layout for intuitive flow
**Description:** The current layout is a shitshow with repetitive sections and unclear hierarchy. Redesign to: LEFT=Task Library (compact, icon+title only, expandable), CENTRE=Command Surface (ranked tasks + prompt composer + today's schedule stacked vertically, clear section headers), RIGHT=Context Drawer (collapsible, only shows when a task is selected or quiz is active). Reduce visual noise by 60%.

**Acceptance criteria:**
- Left column is max 220px, shows task list as compact rows (icon, title, urgency dot, due date) — no expanded detail cards in left panel
- Center column has three clear sections: 'Next Up' (top 3 ranked tasks with action buttons), 'Today's Plan' (schedule blocks), 'Command' (prompt input at bottom) — each with a small section header
- Right panel is hidden by default, slides in when user selects a task or clicks 'Context' — shows task detail + relevant context snippets
- No repeated task information across columns — each piece of data appears exactly once
- All column widths have sensible min/max constraints (left: 180–260, right: 260–360)
- App builds without errors

**Implementation notes:**
This is a major ContentView.swift restructure. Key changes: (1) Left panel becomes a flat list — remove the nested VStack card per task, use a plain List with compact row height. (2) Center panel uses a VStack with three named sections — pin 'Next Up' to top, 'Today's Plan' scrollable middle, 'Command' pinned to bottom. (3) Right panel uses a slide-in animation driven by @State selectedTask: PlannerTask?. When selectedTask != nil, show task detail + context. (4) Remove all the duplicate import/context panels that currently appear in both columns. (5) Section headers should be 11px uppercase tracking-wide labels. (6) Use a thin 1px Divider() between sections, not padding.

